<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>EUCHARISTIC PRAYER II (Consecration and Acclamation - a)</B></FONT></H2>
<H3><PRE>
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.  You are indeed Holy, O Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    the fount of all holiness.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    Make holy, therefore, these gifts, we pray,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    by sending down your Spirit upon them like the
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    dewfall,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    so that they may become for us
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    the Body and Blood of our Lord Jesus Christ.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.  At the time he was betrayed,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and entered willingly into his Passion, 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    he took bread
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                 F                 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and, giving thanks, broke it, 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">         Gm                     Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and gave to his disciples, saying:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                              A7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    TAKE THIS ALL OF YOU, AND EAT FROM IT,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">        Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    FOR THIS IS MY BODY
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">           A7                  Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    WHICH WILL BE GIVEN UP FOR YOU.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    In a similar way,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    when supper was ended,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    he took the chalice
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">               F
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and, once more giving thanks,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">        Gm                   Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    he gave to his disciples saying:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               A7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    TAKE THIS ALL OF YOU, AND DRINK FROM IT,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">        Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    FOR THIS IS THE CHALICE OF MY BLOOD,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">          A7                          Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    THE BLOOD OF THE NEW AND ETERNAL COVENANT,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                               A7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    WHICH WILL BE POURED OUT FOR YOU AND FOR MANY
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">               Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    FOR THE FORGIVENESS OF SINS.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">        A7     Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    DO THIS IN MEMORY OF ME.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Gm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    The mystery
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">        A7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    of faith:

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  We proclaim your Death, O Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Gm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and profess your Resurrection, 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">           A7         Gm         A7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    Maranatha! Maranatha! Maranatha!

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Dm
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  Maranatha!
